# Macro Signal Engine: Hard Constraints

## Competition Rules
- inference.py must use the OpenAI client only. No anthropic, transformers, or local models.
- Required env vars: API_BASE_URL, MODEL_NAME, HF_TOKEN. Never hardcode these.
- Total inference.py runtime must be under 20 minutes across all 3 tasks.
- Stay within 2 vCPU and 8 GB RAM. No scipy, statsmodels, torch, or heavy libraries.
- All rewards must be floats in [0.0, 1.0]. Assert this at every grader return point.
- Three tasks required: single_event (easy), regime_shift (medium), causal_chain (hard).
- Graders must be deterministic. No random seeds at grader call time.

## OpenEnv Spec
- Port is always read from os.environ["PORT"], defaulting to 7860 for HF Spaces. Never hardcode 8000.
- Dockerfile must use a non-root user (useradd / USER user). HF Spaces will reject builds without this.
- WebSocket (/ws) is the primary transport. HTTP /reset and /step are for debug use only.
- openenv.yaml must be present and valid. Checked by openenv validate.
- All Pydantic models use ConfigDict(frozen=True).

## Dependency Direction
- models.py has no local imports.
- client.py imports from models.py only.
- server/environment.py imports from models.py only.
- server/app.py imports from server/environment.py and models.py.
- inference.py imports from client.py and models.py.
- Nothing imports from server/ except app.py.

## Reward Rules
- Every grader function must end with: assert 0.0 <= reward <= 1.0
- Step-level partial rewards are required. Terminal-only rewards will fail the rubric check.
- Idle penalty applies when the agent holds during a step with non-empty signal_events.
- Transaction costs are deducted from NAV, not reward directly.

## Scenario Bank
- data/scenarios.json is the only source of scenario data. No hardcoded scenarios in env code.
- price_path must have exactly max_steps + 1 entries per asset. Validated at startup.
- scenario_id values must be globally unique across all task types.

## Code Style
- No print() in server code. Use logging.
- All async functions live in app.py. All sync logic lives in environment.py.
- Type hints on every function signature.
- No bare except. Always catch specific exception types.
- WORKERS=1 always. Multiple workers break WebSocket session state.
